Thai Cabinet to Discuss Incentives for First-Time Home Buyers

-- B y   S u t t i n e e   Y u v e j w a t t a n a
-- 
2011-09-19T04:49:40Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-19/thai-cabinet-to-discuss-incentives-for-first-time-home-buyers.html
Thailand ’s  Finance Ministry  will
propose a program of tax incentives for first-time home buyers
to the nation’s Cabinet tomorrow, Finance Minister Thirachai
Phuvanatnaranubala said.  Under the proposal, buyers of homes valued at less than 5
million baht would receive tax deductions of as much as 500,000
baht over five years, Thirachai told reporters today in Bankok.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Suttinee Yuvejwattana in Bangkok at 
 suttinee1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
